{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"nvidiaTeslaT4","dataSources":[],"dockerImageVersionId":31329,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":true}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"id":"3cc8f82c-d91d-4eeb-805a-7c7454e17a94","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# 🧠 From VAE to Latent Diffusion: MNIST Digit Generation\n\nA progressive, hands-on notebook covering:\n\n| Chapter | Topic |\n|---------|-------|\n| 1 | Autoencoder Basics |\n| 2 | Variational Autoencoders (VAE) — Theory & Implementation |\n| 3 | Latent Space Exploration & Interpolation |\n| 4 | Flow Matching in the Latent Space |\n| 5 | Denoising Diffusion in the Latent Space (LDM) |\n| 6 | Class-Conditioned Latent Generation |\n\n> **Dataset:** MNIST (28×28 grayscale hand-written digits, 10 classes)  \n> **Framework:** PyTorch  \n> **Recommended runtime:** GPU (CUDA) — CPU works but slower\n","metadata":{}},{"id":"68ef4e7e-5e4c-489d-8d81-10930a1b346d","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 0. Setup & Imports","metadata":{}},{"id":"045d416a-7301-4d39-8715-90662d6d9e7d","cell_type":"code","source":"# Install required packages (uncomment if needed)\n# !pip install torch torchvision matplotlib tqdm einops","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:50:44.275433Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:50:44.275650Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:50:44.279971Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:50:44.275627Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:50:44.279193Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":1},{"id":"0301ede9-1aae-4ffd-af85-0f18a096a9e6","cell_type":"code","source":"import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nimport torch.nn.functional as F\nimport torch.optim as optim\nfrom torch.utils.data import DataLoader\nfrom torchvision import datasets, transforms\nfrom torchvision.utils import make_grid\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport matplotlib.gridspec as gridspec\nfrom tqdm import tqdm\nimport math\n\n# ── reproducibility ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nSEED = 42\ntorch.manual_seed(SEED)\nnp.random.seed(SEED)\n\nDEVICE = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\nprint(f'Using device: {DEVICE}')\n\n# ── global style ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nplt.rcParams.update({\n    'figure.dpi': 120,\n    'axes.facecolor': '#0d0d0d',\n    'figure.facecolor': '#0d0d0d',\n    'axes.titlecolor': '#e0e0e0',\n    'axes.labelcolor': '#b0b0b0',\n    'xtick.color': '#707070',\n    'ytick.color': '#707070',\n    'axes.edgecolor': '#333333',\n    'text.color': '#e0e0e0',\n    'axes.grid': True,\n    'grid.color': '#1e1e1e',\n    'grid.linewidth': 0.6,\n})","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:50:44.281818Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:50:44.282141Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:50:52.867359Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:50:44.282109Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:50:52.866479Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Using device: cuda\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":2},{"id":"c1b30ee0-7e6f-48a2-9c30-9195b2ebfa59","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── MNIST DataLoaders ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ntransform = transforms.Compose([\n    transforms.ToTensor(),          # → [0, 1]\n])\n\ntrain_ds = datasets.MNIST('./data', train=True,  download=True, transform=transform)\ntest_ds  = datasets.MNIST('./data', train=False, download=True, transform=transform)\n\nBATCH = 256\ntrain_loader = DataLoader(train_ds, batch_size=BATCH, shuffle=True,  num_workers=2, pin_memory=True)\ntest_loader  = DataLoader(test_ds,  batch_size=BATCH, shuffle=False, num_workers=2, pin_memory=True)\n\nprint(f'Train: {len(train_ds):,} samples  |  Test: {len(test_ds):,} samples')\n\n# ── peek at the data ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nimgs, labels = next(iter(train_loader))\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 10, figsize=(14, 3))\nfor i, ax in enumerate(axes.flat):\n    ax.imshow(imgs[i].squeeze(), cmap='magma', vmin=0, vmax=1)\n    ax.set_title(str(labels[i].item()), fontsize=8, color='#aaaaaa')\n    ax.axis('off')\nfig.suptitle('MNIST Samples', color='#e0e0e0', y=1.02)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:50:52.868422Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:50:52.868987Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:50:55.645258Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:50:52.868949Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:50:55.644496Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"100%|██████████| 9.91M/9.91M [00:00<00:00, 57.1MB/s]\n100%|██████████| 28.9k/28.9k [00:00<00:00, 1.65MB/s]\n100%|██████████| 1.65M/1.65M [00:00<00:00, 14.6MB/s]\n100%|██████████| 4.54k/4.54k [00:00<00:00, 10.9MB/s]","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"Train: 60,000 samples  |  Test: 10,000 samples\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1680x360 with 20 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":3},{"id":"2eb1a1f1-be33-416a-b4ca-3fcb2913b7c7","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## Chapter 1 — Autoencoder Basics\n\n### 1.1 What is an Autoencoder?\n\nAn **autoencoder** is a neural network trained to copy its input to its output through a *bottleneck*.\n\n```\nInput x  ──►  Encoder f  ──►  z (latent code)  ──►  Decoder g  ──►  x̂ ≈ x\n             (compress)                               (reconstruct)\n```\n\nThe bottleneck forces the network to learn a compact, meaningful representation.\n\n**Loss:** Reconstruction loss only (e.g., MSE or Binary Cross-Entropy)\n\n$$\\mathcal{L}_{AE} = \\|x - \\hat{x}\\|^2$$\n\n### 1.2 Problem with plain AE for generation\n\nThe latent space of a plain AE is **unstructured** — there's no guarantee that sampling from it produces valid images.  \n→ This motivates the **Variational Autoencoder**.","metadata":{}},{"id":"c804c0fe-0163-4e17-8874-1d30f915ca11","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Chapter 1 — Plain Autoencoder\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nclass PlainEncoder(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, latent_dim: int = 16):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.net = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Flatten(),\n            nn.Linear(784, 512), nn.ReLU(),\n            nn.Linear(512, 256), nn.ReLU(),\n            nn.Linear(256, latent_dim),\n        )\n    def forward(self, x): return self.net(x)\n\nclass PlainDecoder(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, latent_dim: int = 16):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.net = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(latent_dim, 256), nn.ReLU(),\n            nn.Linear(256, 512),        nn.ReLU(),\n            nn.Linear(512, 784),        nn.Sigmoid(),\n        )\n    def forward(self, z): return self.net(z).view(-1, 1, 28, 28)\n\nclass AutoEncoder(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, latent_dim: int = 16):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.encoder = PlainEncoder(latent_dim)\n        self.decoder = PlainDecoder(latent_dim)\n    def forward(self, x):\n        z    = self.encoder(x)\n        x_hat = self.decoder(z)\n        return x_hat, z\n\n\n# ── training loop helper ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndef train_ae(model, loader, optimizer, epochs=5, device=DEVICE):\n    model.train()\n    history = []\n    for ep in range(1, epochs + 1):\n        total_loss = 0\n        for x, _ in tqdm(loader, desc=f'AE Epoch {ep}/{epochs}', leave=False):\n            x = x.to(device)\n            x_hat, _ = model(x)\n            loss = F.mse_loss(x_hat, x)\n            optimizer.zero_grad()\n            loss.backward()\n            optimizer.step()\n            total_loss += loss.item() * x.size(0)\n        epoch_loss = total_loss / len(loader.dataset)\n        history.append(epoch_loss)\n        print(f'  Epoch {ep:02d} | Recon Loss: {epoch_loss:.5f}')\n    return history\n\n\nae = AutoEncoder(latent_dim=16).to(DEVICE)\nae_opt = optim.Adam(ae.parameters(), lr=1e-3)\nae_history = train_ae(ae, train_loader, ae_opt, epochs=5)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:50:55.646436Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:50:55.646758Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.139373Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:50:55.646723Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.138417Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                               \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 01 | Recon Loss: 0.05569\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                               \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 02 | Recon Loss: 0.02434\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                               \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 03 | Recon Loss: 0.01852\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                               \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 04 | Recon Loss: 0.01603\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                               ","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 05 | Recon Loss: 0.01442\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"\r","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":4},{"id":"55bf6960-0e90-4049-ac44-5c3a2a9c27a4","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Visualise AE reconstructions ──────────────────────────────────────────────\nae.eval()\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    x_test, _ = next(iter(test_loader))\n    x_test = x_test[:10].to(DEVICE)\n    x_hat, z = ae(x_test)\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 10, figsize=(14, 3))\nfor i in range(10):\n    axes[0, i].imshow(x_test[i].cpu().squeeze(), cmap='magma')\n    axes[0, i].axis('off')\n    axes[1, i].imshow(x_hat[i].cpu().squeeze(), cmap='magma')\n    axes[1, i].axis('off')\naxes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Original', color='#aaa', rotation=90)\naxes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Recon',    color='#aaa', rotation=90)\nfig.suptitle('AutoEncoder — Reconstructions', color='#e0e0e0')\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()\n\nprint(f'Latent dim: {z.shape[1]}  |  Latent mean: {z.mean():.3f}  |  Latent std: {z.std():.3f}')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.140905Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.141563Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.571745Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.141529Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.570755Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1680x360 with 20 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","text":"Latent dim: 16  |  Latent mean: -2.123  |  Latent std: 5.345\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":5},{"id":"8872335d-7a91-4887-8b86-8ecea2582770","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── AE: try random generation (will look messy!) ──────────────────────────────\nae.eval()\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    z_random = torch.randn(20, 16).to(DEVICE)   # sample from N(0,I)\n    imgs_random = ae.decoder(z_random)\n\ngrid = make_grid(imgs_random.cpu(), nrow=10, padding=2)\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 3))\nax.imshow(grid.permute(1, 2, 0).squeeze(), cmap='magma')\nax.axis('off')\nax.set_title('AE: Generating from random N(0,I) samples — unstructured latent space!',\n             color='#ff7043')\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.573532Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.574480Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.683093Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.574415Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.682532Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1440x360 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":6},{"id":"4b77febb-f505-49ce-813d-e0f2ec7dcf51","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## Chapter 2 — Variational Autoencoder (VAE)\n\n### 2.1 Motivation\n\nWe want a **generative model**: sample $z \\sim p(z)$, decode to $p_\\theta(x|z)$.  \nBut the plain AE latent space has **holes** — most random $z$ produce garbage.\n\n### 2.2 VAE Objective — the ELBO\n\nA VAE learns a **posterior** $q_\\phi(z|x) = \\mathcal{N}(\\mu_\\phi(x),\\, \\sigma^2_\\phi(x)\\,I)$  \nand maximises the **Evidence Lower BOund (ELBO)**:\n\n$$\\mathcal{L}_{VAE} = \\underbrace{\\mathbb{E}_{q_\\phi(z|x)}[\\log p_\\theta(x|z)]}_{\\text{reconstruction}} - \\underbrace{D_{KL}(q_\\phi(z|x)\\, \\|\\, p(z))}_{\\text{KL regularisation}}$$\n\nWith $p(z) = \\mathcal{N}(0, I)$ the KL term has a closed form:\n\n$$D_{KL} = -\\frac{1}{2} \\sum_j \\left(1 + \\log\\sigma_j^2 - \\mu_j^2 - \\sigma_j^2\\right)$$\n\n### 2.3 Reparameterisation Trick\n\nTo back-propagate through sampling we write:\n$$z = \\mu + \\sigma \\odot \\epsilon, \\quad \\epsilon \\sim \\mathcal{N}(0, I)$$\n\nThis moves randomness *outside* the computation graph.","metadata":{}},{"id":"77913cb4-7689-49a8-ba74-73bbdd710e4d","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Chapter 2 — VAE\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nLATENT_DIM = 16\n\nclass VAEEncoder(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"Maps x → (μ, log σ²) \"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, latent_dim=LATENT_DIM):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.shared = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Flatten(),\n            nn.Linear(784, 512), nn.SiLU(),\n            nn.Linear(512, 256), nn.SiLU(),\n        )\n        self.fc_mu     = nn.Linear(256, latent_dim)\n        self.fc_logvar = nn.Linear(256, latent_dim)\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        h      = self.shared(x)\n        mu     = self.fc_mu(h)\n        logvar = self.fc_logvar(h)\n        return mu, logvar\n\n\nclass VAEDecoder(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"Maps z → x̂ ∈ [0,1]^784\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, latent_dim=LATENT_DIM):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.net = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(latent_dim, 256), nn.SiLU(),\n            nn.Linear(256, 512),        nn.SiLU(),\n            nn.Linear(512, 784),        nn.Sigmoid(),\n        )\n    def forward(self, z): return self.net(z).view(-1, 1, 28, 28)\n\n\nclass VAE(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, latent_dim=LATENT_DIM):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.encoder = VAEEncoder(latent_dim)\n        self.decoder = VAEDecoder(latent_dim)\n        self.latent_dim = latent_dim\n\n    def reparameterise(self, mu, logvar):\n        # z = μ + ε·σ,  ε ~ N(0, I)\n        std = torch.exp(0.5 * logvar)\n        eps = torch.randn_like(std)\n        return mu + eps * std\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        mu, logvar = self.encoder(x)\n        z          = self.reparameterise(mu, logvar)\n        x_hat      = self.decoder(z)\n        return x_hat, mu, logvar, z\n\n    @torch.no_grad()\n    def sample(self, n, device=DEVICE):\n        z = torch.randn(n, self.latent_dim).to(device)\n        return self.decoder(z)\n\n\ndef vae_loss(x, x_hat, mu, logvar, beta=1.0):\n    \"\"\"ELBO = Recon + β·KL  (β-VAE generalisation)\"\"\"\n    # Binary cross-entropy reconstruction (per pixel, summed per image)\n    recon = F.binary_cross_entropy(x_hat, x, reduction='sum') / x.size(0)\n    # Closed-form KL: -½ Σ(1 + log σ² - μ² - σ²)\n    kl    = -0.5 * torch.sum(1 + logvar - mu.pow(2) - logvar.exp()) / x.size(0)\n    return recon + beta * kl, recon, kl\n\n\nprint('VAE model:')\nvae = VAE(latent_dim=LATENT_DIM).to(DEVICE)\ntotal_params = sum(p.numel() for p in vae.parameters())\nprint(f'  Latent dim : {LATENT_DIM}')\nprint(f'  Parameters : {total_params:,}')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.688230Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.688597Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.712761Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.688573Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.712084Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"VAE model:\n  Latent dim : 16\n  Parameters : 1,079,600\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"id":"554f6bd7-d162-4124-bf50-53883567ac9f","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── VAE Training ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ndef train_vae(model, loader, optimizer, epochs=20, beta=1.0, device=DEVICE):\n    model.train()\n    history = {'total': [], 'recon': [], 'kl': []}\n    for ep in range(1, epochs + 1):\n        tot_total = tot_recon = tot_kl = 0\n        for x, _ in tqdm(loader, desc=f'VAE Epoch {ep}/{epochs}', leave=False):\n            x = x.to(device)\n            x_hat, mu, logvar, _ = model(x)\n            loss, recon, kl = vae_loss(x, x_hat, mu, logvar, beta=beta)\n            optimizer.zero_grad()\n            loss.backward()\n            optimizer.step()\n            n = x.size(0)\n            tot_total += loss.item() * n\n            tot_recon += recon.item() * n\n            tot_kl    += kl.item()   * n\n        N = len(loader.dataset)\n        history['total'].append(tot_total / N)\n        history['recon'].append(tot_recon / N)\n        history['kl'].append(tot_kl / N)\n        if ep % 5 == 0:\n            print(f'  Epoch {ep:02d} | Loss: {history[\"total\"][-1]:.1f} '\n                  f'(Recon {history[\"recon\"][-1]:.1f}  KL {history[\"kl\"][-1]:.2f})')\n    return history\n\n\nvae_opt = optim.Adam(vae.parameters(), lr=1e-3)\nvae_history = train_vae(vae, train_loader, vae_opt, epochs=20, beta=1.0)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.713629Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.713928Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:52:38.958379Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:51:16.713905Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:52:38.957433Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                                 \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 05 | Loss: 115.1 (Recon 99.2  KL 15.83)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                                  \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 10 | Loss: 106.4 (Recon 89.2  KL 17.25)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                                  \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 15 | Loss: 102.2 (Recon 83.9  KL 18.28)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                                  ","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 20 | Loss: 100.2 (Recon 81.6  KL 18.64)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"\r","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":8},{"id":"1df72863-892a-443f-9f21-11482db56856","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Plot training curves ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(14, 4))\ncolors = ['#7c83fd', '#ff6b6b', '#ffd166']\nfor ax, key, col in zip(axes, ['total', 'recon', 'kl'], colors):\n    ax.plot(vae_history[key], color=col, lw=2)\n    ax.set_title(key.upper(), color=col)\n    ax.set_xlabel('Epoch')\nplt.suptitle('VAE Training Loss', color='#e0e0e0', fontsize=13)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:52:38.959697Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:52:38.960084Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:52:39.345573Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:52:38.960054Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:52:39.344688Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1680x480 with 3 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":9},{"id":"34fef954-a22b-452f-beff-50f00c2f71a2","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── VAE reconstructions ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nvae.eval()\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    x_t, _ = next(iter(test_loader))\n    x_t = x_t[:10].to(DEVICE)\n    x_hat, mu, logvar, z = vae(x_t)\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 10, figsize=(14, 3))\nfor i in range(10):\n    axes[0, i].imshow(x_t[i].cpu().squeeze(), cmap='magma');  axes[0, i].axis('off')\n    axes[1, i].imshow(x_hat[i].cpu().squeeze(), cmap='magma'); axes[1, i].axis('off')\naxes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Original', color='#aaa')\naxes[1, 0].set_ylabel('VAE Recon', color='#7c83fd')\nfig.suptitle('VAE — Reconstructions', color='#e0e0e0')\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\n\n# ── VAE samples from prior ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\nsamples = vae.sample(20)\ngrid = make_grid(samples.cpu(), nrow=10, padding=2)\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 3))\nax.imshow(grid.permute(1, 2, 0).squeeze(), cmap='magma')\nax.axis('off')\nax.set_title('VAE — Samples from N(0, I) prior', color='#7c83fd')\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:52:39.346532Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:52:39.346735Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:52:39.844926Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:52:39.346715Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:52:39.844153Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1680x360 with 20 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1440x360 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":10},{"id":"85f1447a-a0b6-4de7-a326-13b74feb9603","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## Chapter 3 — Latent Space Exploration\n\nOne of the most striking properties of a well-trained VAE is its **smooth, structured latent space**.\n\nWe'll visualise it three ways:\n1. **2-D projection** with t-SNE, coloured by digit class\n2. **Latent grid** — decode a 2-D grid of points (for 2-D latent VAE)\n3. **Interpolation** — walk from digit A to digit B through the latent space","metadata":{}},{"id":"9655ed5e-354f-4944-9950-1f57832069be","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Collect latent codes for the test set ─────────────────────────────────────\nfrom sklearn.manifold import TSNE\n\nvae.eval()\nall_mu, all_labels = [], []\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    for x, y in test_loader:\n        mu, _ = vae.encoder(x.to(DEVICE))\n        all_mu.append(mu.cpu())\n        all_labels.append(y)\n\nall_mu     = torch.cat(all_mu).numpy()       # (10000, 16)\nall_labels = torch.cat(all_labels).numpy()   # (10000,)\n\nprint('Running t-SNE (may take ~30 s on CPU)…')\ntsne = TSNE(n_components=2, perplexity=30, random_state=SEED)\nemb  = tsne.fit_transform(all_mu)\n\n# plot\ncmap = plt.cm.get_cmap('tab10', 10)\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 7))\nfor digit in range(10):\n    mask = all_labels == digit\n    ax.scatter(emb[mask, 0], emb[mask, 1], s=4, alpha=0.6,\n               color=cmap(digit), label=str(digit))\nax.legend(title='Digit', markerscale=4, fontsize=8,\n          facecolor='#1a1a1a', edgecolor='#333')\nax.set_title('t-SNE of VAE Latent Space (μ)', color='#e0e0e0', fontsize=13)\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:52:39.846247Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:52:39.847075Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:53:32.677491Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:52:39.847033Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:53:32.676528Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Running t-SNE (may take ~30 s on CPU)…\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"/tmp/ipykernel_55/449857808.py:20: MatplotlibDeprecationWarning: The get_cmap function was deprecated in Matplotlib 3.7 and will be removed in 3.11. Use ``matplotlib.colormaps[name]`` or ``matplotlib.colormaps.get_cmap()`` or ``pyplot.get_cmap()`` instead.\n  cmap = plt.cm.get_cmap('tab10', 10)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1080x840 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":11},{"id":"86db8be7-274e-46cf-8cb4-8c632acc5575","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── 2-D VAE: latent grid ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Train a small 2-D VAE so we can sweep the full latent plane\n\nvae2 = VAE(latent_dim=2).to(DEVICE)\nopt2 = optim.Adam(vae2.parameters(), lr=1e-3)\n_ = train_vae(vae2, train_loader, opt2, epochs=20, beta=1.0)\n\n# decode a grid of z values\nN = 20\ngrid_vals = np.linspace(-2.5, 2.5, N)\ncanvas = np.zeros((28 * N, 28 * N))\n\nvae2.eval()\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    for i, yi in enumerate(grid_vals[::-1]):\n        for j, xi in enumerate(grid_vals):\n            z = torch.tensor([[xi, yi]], dtype=torch.float32).to(DEVICE)\n            img = vae2.decoder(z).cpu().squeeze().numpy()\n            canvas[i*28:(i+1)*28, j*28:(j+1)*28] = img\n\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 10))\nax.imshow(canvas, cmap='magma', origin='upper',\n          extent=[-2.5, 2.5, -2.5, 2.5])\nax.set_xlabel('z₁', fontsize=11)\nax.set_ylabel('z₂', fontsize=11)\nax.set_title('2-D VAE Latent Space Sweep', color='#e0e0e0', fontsize=13)\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:53:32.678851Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:53:32.679553Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:54:57.448457Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:53:32.679520Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:54:57.446604Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                                 \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 05 | Loss: 150.8 (Recon 144.8  KL 5.99)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                                  \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 10 | Loss: 144.4 (Recon 138.1  KL 6.32)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                                  \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 15 | Loss: 141.7 (Recon 135.2  KL 6.48)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"                                                                  \r","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 20 | Loss: 139.9 (Recon 133.3  KL 6.60)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1200x1200 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":12},{"id":"0f7d52fe-b6c4-4ae6-b66d-ddfa7bc672f1","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Latent Interpolation ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Pick two test images from different classes and interpolate in latent space\n\ndef get_latent(model, x):\n    model.eval()\n    with torch.no_grad():\n        # Encode the image to get the mean (mu) of the latent distribution\n        mu, _ = model.encoder(x.unsqueeze(0).to(DEVICE))\n    return mu\n\n# Find a '2' and a '7' - Corrected loop\ncls_imgs = {}\nfor x, y in test_ds:\n    c = y  # Removed .item() because y is already an int\n    if c not in cls_imgs: \n        cls_imgs[c] = x\n    if len(cls_imgs) == 10: \n        break\n\n# Get latent vectors for the start and end points\nz_a = get_latent(vae, cls_imgs[2])\nz_b = get_latent(vae, cls_imgs[7])\n\nsteps = 12\nalphas = torch.linspace(0, 1, steps)\ninterp_imgs = []\n\nvae.eval()\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    for alpha in alphas:\n        # Linear interpolation: z = (1 - alpha) * z_a + alpha * z_b\n        z_interp = (1 - alpha) * z_a + alpha * z_b\n        img = vae.decoder(z_interp)\n        interp_imgs.append(img.cpu())\n\n# Visualization\ninterp_tensor = torch.cat(interp_imgs)\ngrid = make_grid(interp_tensor, nrow=steps, padding=2)\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 2))\nax.imshow(grid.permute(1, 2, 0).squeeze(), cmap='magma')\nax.axis('off')\nax.set_title('Latent Space Interpolation: \"2\" → \"7\"', color='#ffd166')\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:57:48.998488Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:57:48.999189Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:57:49.114977Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:57:48.999157Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:57:49.114338Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1680x240 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":14},{"id":"feee9336-75f6-4520-b727-bfcd5fc35330","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## Chapter 4 — Flow Matching in the Latent Space\n\n### 4.1 What is Flow Matching?\n\nFlow Matching (Lipman et al., 2022) trains a **vector field** $v_\\theta(z, t)$ that transports noise $z_0 \\sim \\mathcal{N}(0, I)$ to data $z_1$ along **straight conditional paths**:\n\n$$z_t = (1-t)\\,z_0 + t\\,z_1, \\qquad t \\in [0, 1]$$\n\n**Training objective** — Conditional Flow Matching (CFM):\n$$\\mathcal{L}_{CFM} = \\mathbb{E}_{t,z_0,z_1} \\left\\| v_\\theta(z_t, t) - (z_1 - z_0) \\right\\|^2$$\n\nThe target velocity is simply $z_1 - z_0$ (pointing from noise to data).\n\n**Inference:** Euler integration (or ODE solver) from $t=0$ to $t=1$:\n$$z_{t+\\Delta t} = z_t + \\Delta t \\cdot v_\\theta(z_t, t)$$\n\n### 4.2 Why Flow Matching over Diffusion?\n\n| | Diffusion (DDPM) | Flow Matching |\n|---|---|---|\n| Training | Predict noise $\\epsilon$ | Predict velocity $v$ |\n| Paths | Curved (SDE) | Straight (ODE) |\n| Steps needed | 100–1000 | 10–50 |\n| Mode coverage | Good | Excellent |\n\n### 4.3 Latent Flow Matching\n\nInstead of operating in pixel space, we:\n1. Encode MNIST → VAE latent $z_1 = \\mu_\\phi(x)$\n2. Train a flow network $v_\\theta(z_t, t)$ in **latent space** to go from $\\mathcal{N}(0,I)$ to the latent distribution\n3. At generation: integrate ODE → $\\hat{z}_1$ → decode with VAE decoder","metadata":{}},{"id":"a48848bf-3c6f-491a-85c4-a0f2554eaca3","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Chapter 4 — Flow Matching in the Latent Space\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n# ── Step 4.1: collect all latent codes (μ) from trained VAE ──────────────────\nvae.eval()\nlatent_bank, label_bank = [], []\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    for x, y in train_loader:\n        mu, _ = vae.encoder(x.to(DEVICE))\n        latent_bank.append(mu.cpu())\n        label_bank.append(y)\n\nlatent_bank = torch.cat(latent_bank)   # (60000, 16)\nlabel_bank  = torch.cat(label_bank)    # (60000,)\nprint(f'Latent bank: {latent_bank.shape}  mean={latent_bank.mean():.3f}  std={latent_bank.std():.3f}')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:57:51.822612Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:57:51.823415Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:57:56.134468Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:57:51.823382Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:57:56.133490Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Latent bank: torch.Size([60000, 16])  mean=-0.000  std=0.790\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":15},{"id":"1118364c-9a17-4742-95bc-0c22b97a13dc","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Step 4.2: Flow Matching network ──────────────────────────────────────────\n\nclass SinusoidalEmbedding(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"Encode scalar t ∈ [0,1] with sinusoidal frequencies.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, dim=128):\n        super().__init__()\n        assert dim % 2 == 0\n        self.dim = dim\n    def forward(self, t):\n        # t: (B,)  → (B, dim)\n        half = self.dim // 2\n        freqs = torch.exp(\n            -math.log(10000) * torch.arange(half, device=t.device) / (half - 1)\n        )\n        angles = t[:, None] * freqs[None]  # (B, half)\n        return torch.cat([angles.sin(), angles.cos()], dim=-1)  # (B, dim)\n\n\nclass VelocityNet(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"v_θ(z_t, t) → velocity in latent space\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, latent_dim=LATENT_DIM, hidden=256, t_emb_dim=128):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.t_embed = SinusoidalEmbedding(t_emb_dim)\n        self.net = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(latent_dim + t_emb_dim, hidden), nn.SiLU(),\n            nn.Linear(hidden, hidden),                  nn.SiLU(),\n            nn.Linear(hidden, hidden),                  nn.SiLU(),\n            nn.Linear(hidden, latent_dim),\n        )\n    def forward(self, z, t):\n        t_emb = self.t_embed(t)\n        x     = torch.cat([z, t_emb], dim=-1)\n        return self.net(x)\n\n\n# ── Step 4.3: CFM training loop ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ndef train_flow(net, latent_bank, optimizer, epochs=200, batch=512, device=DEVICE):\n    net.train()\n    N = latent_bank.shape[0]\n    history = []\n    for ep in range(1, epochs + 1):\n        # random mini-batch of data latents\n        idx    = torch.randperm(N)[:batch]\n        z1     = latent_bank[idx].to(device)          # (B, latent_dim)\n        z0     = torch.randn_like(z1)                 # noise sample\n        t      = torch.rand(batch, device=device)     # t ~ Uniform[0,1]\n\n        # straight-line path\n        zt     = (1 - t[:, None]) * z0 + t[:, None] * z1\n        target = z1 - z0                               # target velocity\n\n        v_pred = net(zt, t)\n        loss   = F.mse_loss(v_pred, target)\n\n        optimizer.zero_grad()\n        loss.backward()\n        optimizer.step()\n        history.append(loss.item())\n        if ep % 50 == 0:\n            print(f'  Epoch {ep:04d} | CFM Loss: {loss.item():.6f}')\n    return history\n\n\nflow_net = VelocityNet(latent_dim=LATENT_DIM).to(DEVICE)\nflow_opt = optim.Adam(flow_net.parameters(), lr=5e-4)\nflow_history = train_flow(flow_net, latent_bank, flow_opt, epochs=500, batch=512)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:57:56.136137Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:57:56.136533Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:57:57.963061Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:57:56.136503Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:57:57.962323Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 0050 | CFM Loss: 1.399291\n  Epoch 0100 | CFM Loss: 1.341174\n  Epoch 0150 | CFM Loss: 1.373138\n  Epoch 0200 | CFM Loss: 1.314401\n  Epoch 0250 | CFM Loss: 1.325493\n  Epoch 0300 | CFM Loss: 1.228230\n  Epoch 0350 | CFM Loss: 1.217620\n  Epoch 0400 | CFM Loss: 1.261878\n  Epoch 0450 | CFM Loss: 1.184461\n  Epoch 0500 | CFM Loss: 1.187780\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":16},{"id":"e8274f8e-046f-4f56-9336-356a950c4f08","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Step 4.4: Euler ODE integration → decode ─────────────────────────────────\n\n@torch.no_grad()\ndef flow_sample(net, decoder, n=16, steps=50, device=DEVICE):\n    \"\"\"Integrate ODE from t=0 (noise) to t=1 (data).\"\"\"\n    net.eval(); decoder.eval()\n    z = torch.randn(n, LATENT_DIM).to(device)   # z_0 ~ N(0,I)\n    dt = 1.0 / steps\n    for i in range(steps):\n        t_val = torch.full((n,), i * dt, device=device)\n        v     = net(z, t_val)\n        z     = z + dt * v\n    return decoder(z)\n\n\nsamples = flow_sample(flow_net, vae.decoder, n=20, steps=50)\ngrid    = make_grid(samples.cpu(), nrow=10, padding=2)\n\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 3))\nax.imshow(grid.permute(1, 2, 0).squeeze(), cmap='magma')\nax.axis('off')\nax.set_title('Flow Matching in Latent Space → Decoded Digits', color='#a0e4b0')\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:57:57.964162Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:57:57.964616Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.089212Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:57:57.964587Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.088589Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1440x360 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":17},{"id":"e59db4a0-39c6-4ea4-b5a2-8ffbb1f86d2e","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Visualise the ODE trajectory ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Show how a single latent code evolves from pure noise to a digit\n\n@torch.no_grad()\ndef flow_trajectory(net, decoder, n=1, steps=12, device=DEVICE):\n    net.eval(); decoder.eval()\n    z = torch.randn(n, LATENT_DIM).to(device)\n    trajectory = []\n    dt = 1.0 / steps\n    for i in range(steps + 1):\n        trajectory.append(decoder(z).cpu())\n        if i < steps:\n            t_val = torch.full((n,), i * dt, device=device)\n            z = z + dt * net(z, t_val)\n    return trajectory\n\ntraj = flow_trajectory(flow_net, vae.decoder, n=1, steps=12)\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 13, figsize=(16, 2))\nfor i, (ax, img) in enumerate(zip(axes, traj)):\n    ax.imshow(img.squeeze(), cmap='magma')\n    ax.set_title(f't={i/12:.2f}', fontsize=7, color='#a0e4b0')\n    ax.axis('off')\nfig.suptitle('Flow ODE Trajectory: Noise → Digit', color='#e0e0e0')\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.090837Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.091149Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.521330Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.091126Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.520684Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1920x240 with 13 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":18},{"id":"878d2de3-2409-4b1f-a430-9a11ba009311","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## Chapter 5 — Latent Diffusion (DDPM in Latent Space)\n\n### 5.1 DDPM Recap\n\n**Denoising Diffusion Probabilistic Models** (Ho et al., 2020) define:\n\n- **Forward process** — gradually add Gaussian noise over $T$ steps:\n$$q(z_t | z_{t-1}) = \\mathcal{N}(z_t;\\, \\sqrt{1-\\beta_t}\\, z_{t-1},\\, \\beta_t I)$$\n\n  Closed form at any step $t$:\n$$q(z_t | z_0) = \\mathcal{N}(z_t;\\, \\sqrt{\\bar\\alpha_t}\\, z_0,\\, (1-\\bar\\alpha_t) I)$$\n  where $\\bar\\alpha_t = \\prod_{s=1}^t (1-\\beta_s)$.\n\n- **Reverse process** — learn to remove noise:\n$$p_\\theta(z_{t-1} | z_t) = \\mathcal{N}(z_{t-1};\\, \\mu_\\theta(z_t, t),\\, \\Sigma_t)$$\n\n- **Training** — predict the noise added at step $t$:\n$$\\mathcal{L} = \\mathbb{E}_{t, z_0, \\epsilon}\\left[ \\|\\epsilon - \\epsilon_\\theta(z_t, t)\\|^2 \\right]$$\n\n### 5.2 Latent Diffusion\n\n**Latent Diffusion Models** (Rombach et al., 2022) run DDPM entirely in the VAE's latent space:\n\n```\nx ──► VAE Encoder ──► z₀  (latent)\n                       │\n              DDPM forward/reverse in latent space\n                       │\n              ẑ₀ ──► VAE Decoder ──► x̂\n```\n\nBenefits: **much smaller** diffusion network, **faster** training & inference.\n","metadata":{}},{"id":"dabf73ac-d539-462c-8bfe-686564d61743","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Chapter 5 — Latent Diffusion (DDPM)\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n# ── 5.1  Noise schedule ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nclass DiffusionScheduler:\n    \"\"\"Cosine noise schedule (Nichol & Dhariwal, 2021).\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, T=1000, s=0.008, device=DEVICE):\n        self.T      = T\n        self.device = device\n\n        steps       = torch.arange(T + 1, dtype=torch.float64)\n        f           = torch.cos((steps / T + s) / (1 + s) * math.pi / 2) ** 2\n        alphas_cumprod = f / f[0]\n        betas       = 1 - alphas_cumprod[1:] / alphas_cumprod[:-1]\n        betas       = betas.clamp(0, 0.999).float().to(device)\n\n        alphas      = 1 - betas\n        self.alpha_bar = torch.cumprod(alphas, dim=0)            # ᾱ_t\n        self.sqrt_alpha_bar    = self.alpha_bar.sqrt()\n        self.sqrt_one_minus_ab = (1 - self.alpha_bar).sqrt()\n\n    def q_sample(self, z0, t, noise=None):\n        \"\"\"Forward: z_t = √ᾱ_t · z₀ + √(1-ᾱ_t) · ε\"\"\"\n        if noise is None: noise = torch.randn_like(z0)\n        sqrt_ab     = self.sqrt_alpha_bar[t][:, None]\n        sqrt_one_m  = self.sqrt_one_minus_ab[t][:, None]\n        return sqrt_ab * z0 + sqrt_one_m * noise, noise\n\n    def p_mean(self, eps_pred, zt, t):\n        \"\"\"DDPM reverse mean: μ_θ(z_t, t)\"\"\"\n        ab   = self.alpha_bar[t][:, None]\n        ab1  = self.alpha_bar[t - 1][:, None].clamp(min=0)\n        beta = 1 - ab / ab1\n        return (zt - beta / (1 - ab).sqrt() * eps_pred) / (1 - beta).sqrt()\n\n\nscheduler = DiffusionScheduler(T=1000)\n\n# ── visualise the schedule ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nab = scheduler.alpha_bar.cpu().numpy()\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 3))\nax.plot(ab, color='#7c83fd', lw=2)\nax.set_xlabel('Diffusion step t')\nax.set_ylabel('ᾱ_t  (signal retention)')\nax.set_title('Cosine Noise Schedule — ᾱ_t', color='#e0e0e0')\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.607641Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.608132Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.803123Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.608106Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.802495Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 960x360 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":19},{"id":"f5a0ee0d-8172-46e5-b768-c422ad036a30","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── 5.2  Denoising U-Net (latent MLP version) ─────────────────────────────────\n\nclass ResBlock(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"Simple residual MLP block with time conditioning.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, dim, t_dim):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.norm   = nn.LayerNorm(dim)\n        self.lin1   = nn.Linear(dim, dim)\n        self.lin2   = nn.Linear(dim, dim)\n        self.t_proj = nn.Linear(t_dim, dim)\n        self.act    = nn.SiLU()\n\n    def forward(self, x, t_emb):\n        h = self.norm(x)\n        h = self.act(self.lin1(h))\n        h = h + self.t_proj(t_emb)\n        h = self.lin2(self.act(h))\n        return x + h\n\n\nclass LatentDenoiser(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"ε_θ(z_t, t) — predicts the noise added at step t.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, latent_dim=LATENT_DIM, hidden=512, t_emb_dim=128, depth=6):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.t_embed  = SinusoidalEmbedding(t_emb_dim)\n        self.t_mlp    = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(t_emb_dim, t_emb_dim * 2), nn.SiLU(),\n                                       nn.Linear(t_emb_dim * 2, t_emb_dim))\n        self.in_proj  = nn.Linear(latent_dim, hidden)\n        self.blocks   = nn.ModuleList([ResBlock(hidden, t_emb_dim) for _ in range(depth)])\n        self.out_proj = nn.Sequential(nn.LayerNorm(hidden),\n                                       nn.Linear(hidden, latent_dim))\n\n    def forward(self, zt, t):\n        t_emb = self.t_mlp(self.t_embed(t.float() / 999))  # normalise t\n        h     = self.in_proj(zt)\n        for blk in self.blocks:\n            h = blk(h, t_emb)\n        return self.out_proj(h)\n\n\ndenoiser = LatentDenoiser(latent_dim=LATENT_DIM).to(DEVICE)\nn_params  = sum(p.numel() for p in denoiser.parameters())\nprint(f'Denoiser parameters: {n_params:,}')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.956518Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.957277Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:57:59.003962Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:57:58.957249Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:57:59.003374Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Denoiser parameters: 3,638,160\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":20},{"id":"243fe563-2718-47f8-934d-cb263e915a21","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── 5.3  Training the latent denoiser ────────────────────────────────────────\n\ndef train_latent_ddpm(denoiser, latent_bank, scheduler, optimizer,\n                      epochs=300, batch=512, device=DEVICE):\n    denoiser.train()\n    N = latent_bank.shape[0]\n    T = scheduler.T\n    history = []\n\n    for ep in range(1, epochs + 1):\n        idx  = torch.randperm(N)[:batch]\n        z0   = latent_bank[idx].to(device)                      # (B, D)\n        t    = torch.randint(1, T, (batch,), device=device)     # t ~ U[1, T)\n\n        zt, noise = scheduler.q_sample(z0, t)                   # noisy latent\n        eps_pred  = denoiser(zt, t)                             # predict noise\n\n        loss = F.mse_loss(eps_pred, noise)\n        optimizer.zero_grad()\n        loss.backward()\n        torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(denoiser.parameters(), 1.0)\n        optimizer.step()\n        history.append(loss.item())\n\n        if ep % 50 == 0:\n            print(f'  Epoch {ep:04d} | Denoising Loss: {loss.item():.6f}')\n\n    return history\n\n\nddpm_opt = optim.Adam(denoiser.parameters(), lr=1e-3)\nddpm_history = train_latent_ddpm(denoiser, latent_bank, scheduler, ddpm_opt,\n                                  epochs=500, batch=512)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:58:01.416978Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:58:01.417547Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.248691Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:58:01.417514Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.247988Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 0050 | Denoising Loss: 0.416932\n  Epoch 0100 | Denoising Loss: 0.334734\n  Epoch 0150 | Denoising Loss: 0.326338\n  Epoch 0200 | Denoising Loss: 0.331224\n  Epoch 0250 | Denoising Loss: 0.299743\n  Epoch 0300 | Denoising Loss: 0.343142\n  Epoch 0350 | Denoising Loss: 0.324953\n  Epoch 0400 | Denoising Loss: 0.306382\n  Epoch 0450 | Denoising Loss: 0.309981\n  Epoch 0500 | Denoising Loss: 0.320922\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":21},{"id":"7bcee6ff-b888-4a4a-b6e3-82a4fd231255","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── 5.4  DDPM sampling (DDPM reverse process) ────────────────────────────────\n\n@torch.no_grad()\ndef ddpm_sample(denoiser, decoder, scheduler, n=16, device=DEVICE):\n    denoiser.eval(); decoder.eval()\n    T   = scheduler.T\n    z   = torch.randn(n, LATENT_DIM).to(device)  # z_T ~ N(0, I)\n\n    for t_step in reversed(range(1, T)):\n        t_tensor = torch.full((n,), t_step, device=device, dtype=torch.long)\n        eps      = denoiser(z, t_tensor)\n        z_mean   = scheduler.p_mean(eps, z, t_tensor)\n\n        if t_step > 1:\n            # variance\n            ab  = scheduler.alpha_bar[t_step]\n            ab1 = scheduler.alpha_bar[t_step - 1]\n            sigma = ((1 - ab1) / (1 - ab) * (1 - ab / ab1)).sqrt()\n            z = z_mean + sigma * torch.randn_like(z)\n        else:\n            z = z_mean\n\n    return decoder(z)\n\n\n@torch.no_grad()\ndef ddim_sample(denoiser, decoder, scheduler, n=16, steps=50, device=DEVICE):\n    \"\"\"DDIM deterministic sampler — much faster than full DDPM.\"\"\"\n    denoiser.eval(); decoder.eval()\n    T    = scheduler.T\n    ts   = torch.linspace(T - 1, 1, steps, dtype=torch.long, device=device)\n    z    = torch.randn(n, LATENT_DIM).to(device)\n\n    for i, t_val in enumerate(ts):\n        t_tensor = t_val.expand(n)\n        eps      = denoiser(z, t_tensor)\n        ab       = scheduler.alpha_bar[t_val]\n        ab_prev  = scheduler.alpha_bar[ts[i + 1]] if i + 1 < len(ts) else torch.tensor(1.0, device=device)\n        z0_pred  = (z - (1 - ab).sqrt() * eps) / ab.sqrt()\n        z0_pred  = z0_pred.clamp(-4, 4)\n        z        = ab_prev.sqrt() * z0_pred + (1 - ab_prev).sqrt() * eps\n\n    return decoder(z)\n\n\n# DDIM is deterministic and only needs 50 steps (vs 999 for full DDPM)\nsamples = ddim_sample(denoiser, vae.decoder, scheduler, n=20, steps=50)\ngrid    = make_grid(samples.cpu(), nrow=10, padding=2)\n\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 3))\nax.imshow(grid.permute(1, 2, 0).squeeze(), cmap='magma')\nax.axis('off')\nax.set_title('Latent Diffusion (DDIM 50 steps) → Decoded Digits', color='#ff6b6b')\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.250153Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.250461Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.452152Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.250437Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.451176Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1440x360 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":22},{"id":"a88b3aa9-d459-4479-9c0f-378ed4fca746","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Visualise denoising trajectory ───────────────────────────────────────────\n@torch.no_grad()\ndef ddim_trajectory(denoiser, decoder, scheduler, n=1, steps=12, device=DEVICE):\n    denoiser.eval(); decoder.eval()\n    T  = scheduler.T\n    ts = torch.linspace(T - 1, 1, steps, dtype=torch.long, device=device)\n    z  = torch.randn(n, LATENT_DIM).to(device)\n    imgs = []\n\n    for i, t_val in enumerate(ts):\n        imgs.append(decoder(z).cpu())\n        t_tensor = t_val.expand(n)\n        eps      = denoiser(z, t_tensor)\n        ab       = scheduler.alpha_bar[t_val]\n        ab_prev  = scheduler.alpha_bar[ts[i + 1]] if i + 1 < len(ts) else torch.tensor(1.0, device=device)\n        z0_pred  = (z - (1 - ab).sqrt() * eps) / ab.sqrt()\n        z        = ab_prev.sqrt() * z0_pred + (1 - ab_prev).sqrt() * eps\n    imgs.append(decoder(z).cpu())\n    return imgs\n\ntraj = ddim_trajectory(denoiser, vae.decoder, scheduler, steps=12)\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 13, figsize=(16, 2))\nfor i, (ax, img) in enumerate(zip(axes, traj)):\n    ax.imshow(img.squeeze(), cmap='magma')\n    ax.set_title(f'step {i}', fontsize=7, color='#ff6b6b')\n    ax.axis('off')\nfig.suptitle('DDIM Latent Denoising Trajectory', color='#e0e0e0')\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.453376Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.453731Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.912004Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.453693Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:58:06.911376Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1920x240 with 13 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":23},{"id":"433a2b6d-bedd-4a2d-8e98-d1da578ac4c5","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## Chapter 6 — Class-Conditioned Latent Generation\n\nWe can guide the denoiser (or flow net) with a class label $c \\in \\{0,\\ldots,9\\}$ using **classifier-free guidance** (Ho & Salimans, 2022):\n\n- Train with label dropout: 10% of the time pass $c = \\varnothing$ (unconditional)\n- At inference, blend unconditional and conditional noise predictions:\n\n$$\\tilde\\epsilon_\\theta(z_t, t, c) = \\epsilon_\\theta(z_t, t, \\varnothing) + \\omega \\cdot (\\epsilon_\\theta(z_t, t, c) - \\epsilon_\\theta(z_t, t, \\varnothing))$$\n\n$\\omega > 1$ is the **guidance scale** — larger = sharper / more class-like, smaller = more diverse.","metadata":{}},{"id":"55f7e9a6-d522-4c7b-b5bc-ac3aa96e6e8e","cell_type":"code","source":"# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n# Chapter 6 — Class-Conditioned Latent Diffusion with CFG\n# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nNUM_CLASSES = 10\nNULL_CLASS  = NUM_CLASSES          # special index for unconditional\n\nclass CondLatentDenoiser(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"ε_θ(z_t, t, c)  with classifier-free guidance support.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, latent_dim=LATENT_DIM, hidden=512, t_emb_dim=128, depth=6):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.t_embed    = SinusoidalEmbedding(t_emb_dim)\n        self.t_mlp      = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(t_emb_dim, t_emb_dim * 2), nn.SiLU(),\n                                         nn.Linear(t_emb_dim * 2, t_emb_dim))\n        # +1 for null class embedding\n        self.class_emb  = nn.Embedding(NUM_CLASSES + 1, t_emb_dim)\n        self.in_proj    = nn.Linear(latent_dim, hidden)\n        self.blocks     = nn.ModuleList([ResBlock(hidden, t_emb_dim) for _ in range(depth)])\n        self.out_proj   = nn.Sequential(nn.LayerNorm(hidden), nn.Linear(hidden, latent_dim))\n\n    def forward(self, zt, t, c):\n        t_emb = self.t_mlp(self.t_embed(t.float() / 999))\n        c_emb = self.class_emb(c)           # (B, t_emb_dim)\n        cond  = t_emb + c_emb               # combine time + class\n        h     = self.in_proj(zt)\n        for blk in self.blocks:\n            h = blk(h, cond)\n        return self.out_proj(h)\n\n\ndef train_cond_ddpm(model, latent_bank, label_bank, scheduler, optimizer,\n                    epochs=500, batch=512, p_uncond=0.1, device=DEVICE):\n    model.train()\n    N = latent_bank.shape[0]\n    T = scheduler.T\n    history = []\n\n    for ep in range(1, epochs + 1):\n        idx   = torch.randperm(N)[:batch]\n        z0    = latent_bank[idx].to(device)\n        c     = label_bank[idx].to(device)\n        t     = torch.randint(1, T, (batch,), device=device)\n\n        # label dropout for classifier-free guidance\n        mask  = torch.rand(batch, device=device) < p_uncond\n        c_in  = torch.where(mask, torch.full_like(c, NULL_CLASS), c)\n\n        zt, noise = scheduler.q_sample(z0, t)\n        eps_pred  = model(zt, t, c_in)\n        loss      = F.mse_loss(eps_pred, noise)\n\n        optimizer.zero_grad()\n        loss.backward()\n        torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), 1.0)\n        optimizer.step()\n        history.append(loss.item())\n\n        if ep % 100 == 0:\n            print(f'  Epoch {ep:04d} | Cond DDPM Loss: {loss.item():.6f}')\n    return history\n\n\ncond_denoiser = CondLatentDenoiser(latent_dim=LATENT_DIM).to(DEVICE)\ncond_opt      = optim.Adam(cond_denoiser.parameters(), lr=1e-3)\ncond_history  = train_cond_ddpm(cond_denoiser, latent_bank, label_bank,\n                                 scheduler, cond_opt, epochs=600)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:58:07.112866Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:58:07.113702Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:58:12.591517Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:58:07.113670Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:58:12.590773Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"  Epoch 0100 | Cond DDPM Loss: 0.324867\n  Epoch 0200 | Cond DDPM Loss: 0.291055\n  Epoch 0300 | Cond DDPM Loss: 0.278901\n  Epoch 0400 | Cond DDPM Loss: 0.294311\n  Epoch 0500 | Cond DDPM Loss: 0.291161\n  Epoch 0600 | Cond DDPM Loss: 0.296086\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":24},{"id":"80313739-293e-4fef-b958-cbb01b74cf65","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── CFG sampling ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n@torch.no_grad()\ndef cfg_ddim_sample(model, decoder, scheduler, label, n=10,\n                    steps=50, guidance=3.0, device=DEVICE):\n    model.eval(); decoder.eval()\n    T    = scheduler.T\n    ts   = torch.linspace(T - 1, 1, steps, dtype=torch.long, device=device)\n    z    = torch.randn(n, LATENT_DIM).to(device)\n    c    = torch.full((n,), label, device=device, dtype=torch.long)\n    null = torch.full((n,), NULL_CLASS, device=device, dtype=torch.long)\n\n    for i, t_val in enumerate(ts):\n        t_t   = t_val.expand(n)\n        eps_c = model(z, t_t, c)\n        eps_u = model(z, t_t, null)\n        eps   = eps_u + guidance * (eps_c - eps_u)   # guided noise\n\n        ab      = scheduler.alpha_bar[t_val]\n        ab_prev = scheduler.alpha_bar[ts[i + 1]] if i + 1 < len(ts) else torch.tensor(1.0, device=device)\n        z0_pred = (z - (1 - ab).sqrt() * eps) / ab.sqrt()\n        z0_pred = z0_pred.clamp(-4, 4)\n        z       = ab_prev.sqrt() * z0_pred + (1 - ab_prev).sqrt() * eps\n\n    return decoder(z)\n\n\n# Generate 5 samples for each digit class\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(10, 5, figsize=(7, 14))\nfor digit in range(10):\n    imgs = cfg_ddim_sample(cond_denoiser, vae.decoder, scheduler,\n                           label=digit, n=5, steps=50, guidance=3.0)\n    for j, ax in enumerate(axes[digit]):\n        ax.imshow(imgs[j].cpu().squeeze(), cmap='magma')\n        ax.axis('off')\n        if j == 0:\n            ax.set_ylabel(f'Digit {digit}', color='#ffd166', rotation=0,\n                          labelpad=32, va='center', fontsize=9)\n\nfig.suptitle('Class-Conditioned Latent Diffusion (CFG ω=3)\\n5 samples per digit',\n             color='#e0e0e0', fontsize=12, y=1.01)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:58:12.593097Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:58:12.593468Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:58:15.166561Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:58:12.593443Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:58:15.165705Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 840x1680 with 50 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":25},{"id":"56324ac7-dc7e-4bba-8213-cca0eb02c0ec","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Guidance scale ablation ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Same noise seed, different guidance scales → more structure vs diversity\n\ntorch.manual_seed(0)\nz_seed = torch.randn(1, LATENT_DIM).to(DEVICE)\n\nguidance_scales = [1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 5.0, 8.0]\nTARGET_DIGIT = 3\n\nrows = []\nfor gs in guidance_scales:\n    imgs = cfg_ddim_sample(cond_denoiser, vae.decoder, scheduler,\n                           label=TARGET_DIGIT, n=8, steps=50, guidance=gs)\n    rows.append(imgs)\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(len(guidance_scales), 8, figsize=(11, 7))\nfor row_i, (gs, imgs) in enumerate(zip(guidance_scales, rows)):\n    for col_i, ax in enumerate(axes[row_i]):\n        ax.imshow(imgs[col_i].cpu().squeeze(), cmap='magma')\n        ax.axis('off')\n    axes[row_i, 0].set_ylabel(f'ω={gs}', color='#a0e4b0', rotation=0,\n                               labelpad=32, va='center', fontsize=9)\n\nfig.suptitle(f'Guidance Scale Ablation — Digit \"{TARGET_DIGIT}\"',\n             color='#e0e0e0', fontsize=12)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T12:58:15.167609Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T12:58:15.167938Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T12:58:16.469153Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T12:58:15.167903Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T12:58:16.468482Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1320x840 with 40 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":26},{"id":"6836d4ca-c213-44c8-89e9-7147da581cc9","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## Summary & Key Takeaways\n\n```\nPlain AE   → learns compact codes, but latent space is unstructured → bad generation\n     │\n     ▼\nVAE        → adds KL regularisation → latent ≈ N(0,I) → smooth generative space\n     │\n     ├──► Flow Matching (CFM) in latent space\n     │         • straight ODE paths from noise to data\n     │         • fast inference (50 Euler steps)\n     │         • simple MSE loss on velocity\n     │\n     └──► Latent Diffusion (DDPM/DDIM) in latent space\n               • curved SDE paths; noise prediction loss\n               • DDIM accelerates to 50 deterministic steps\n               • Class-conditioning + CFG → controllable generation\n```\n\n| Model | Latent space | Generation | Speed | Control |\n|-------|-------------|------------|-------|----------|\n| AE | Unstructured | ❌ | Fast | ❌ |\n| VAE | N(0,I) reg. | ✅ | Fast | ❌ |\n| VAE + Flow | N(0,I) | ✅✅ | Very fast | ✅ |\n| VAE + DDPM | N(0,I) | ✅✅ | Medium | ✅✅ |\n| VAE + DDPM + CFG | N(0,I) | ✅✅✅ | Medium | ✅✅✅ |\n\n### References\n\n1. Kingma & Welling (2013). *Auto-Encoding Variational Bayes*\n2. Ho et al. (2020). *Denoising Diffusion Probabilistic Models*\n3. Song et al. (2021). *Denoising Diffusion Implicit Models*\n4. Nichol & Dhariwal (2021). *Improved Denoising Diffusion Probabilistic Models*\n5. Rombach et al. (2022). *High-Resolution Image Synthesis with Latent Diffusion Models*\n6. Ho & Salimans (2022). *Classifier-Free Diffusion Guidance*\n7. Lipman et al. (2022). *Flow Matching for Generative Modeling*\n8. Albergo & Vanden-Eijnden (2023). *Building Normalizing Flows with Stochastic Interpolants*\n","metadata":{}}]}